[Category:December 1986 sports events in Asia]]\n[[Category:1986 in Tokyo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football match\n|title = 1986 Intercontinental Cup\n|image = ToyotaCup1986.jpg\n|event =\n|team1 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]\n|team1association = {{flagicon|ARG|size=30px}}\n|team1score = 1\n|team2 = [[FCSB|Steaua Bucure\u015fti]]\n|        team2association = {{flagicon|ROU|1965|size=30px}}\n|              team2score = 0\n|                 details =\n|                    date = 14 December 1986\n|                 stadium = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]]\n|                    city = [[Tokyo]]\n|      man_of_the_match1a = [[Antonio Alzamendi]] ([[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]])\n| man_of_the_match1atitle =\n|      man_of_the_match1b =\n| man_of_the_match1btitle =\n|                 referee = [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Mart\u00ednez Baz\u00e1n|Jos\u00e9 Mart\u00ednez]] ([[Asociaci\u00f3n Uruguaya de F\u00fatbol|Uruguay]])\n|              attendance = 62,000\n|                 weather =\n|                previous = [[1985 Intercontinental Cup|1985]]\n|                    next = [[1987 Intercontinental Cup|1987]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1986 Intercontinental Cup''' was a [[Association football|football]] match played on 14 December 1986 between [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]] of [[Argentina]], winners of the [[1986 Copa Libertadores|1986]] [[Copa Libertadores]], and [[FCSB|Steaua Bucure\u015fti]] of [[Romania]], winners of the [[1985\u201386 European Cup|1985\u201386]] [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]. The match was played at the neutral venue of the [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]] in Tokyo in front of 62,000 fans.<ref>{{cite web\n| url        = http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyota86.html\n| title      = Intercontinental Club Cup 1986\n| first      = Osvaldo\n| last       = Gorgazzi\n| publisher  = [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]\n| date       = 16 Jul 2000\n| accessdate = 23 December 2009\n}}</ref> [[Antonio Alzamendi]] was named as [[man of the match]] and got the only goal of the game in the 28th minute when he headed into the net after his initial shot had hit the post and then came back off the goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html |title=Toyota Cup - Most Valuable Player of the Match Award |first=Alzamendi |last=Alzamendi |publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] |date=2 January 2009 |accessdate=23 December 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090414090937/http://rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html |archivedate=14 April 2009 }}</ref> In 2017 FIFA Council recognised all the trophy winners as club world champions with the same title to the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] winners, then as official<ref name=\":F152322\">\"Official (''plural'' officials), from the Latin '' offici\u0101lis.'' 1. The official word is also used to refer to what is recognized or derives from an authority. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/official|title=Official, definition|author=dictionary.com}} 2. Approved by the government or someone in power. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-spanish/official|title=official|author=dictionary.cambridge.org}} It is synonymous with legal, legitimate, approved. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.thesaurus.com/browse/official|title=Synonyms for official|author=thesaurus.com}}</ref><ref name=\":F154232\">For FIFA statute, official competitions are those for representative teams organized by FIFA or any confederation. Representative teams are usually national teams but also club teams that represent a confederation in the interconfederal competitions or a member association in a continental competition cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=5|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/55/82/79/2558279_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=2018/19 UEFA Champions League regulations|page=10}}</ref> \"[[Intercontinental Cup (football)#International participation|world champions]]\" FIFA.<ref name=\":F154233222\">\u201cWhile it does not promote the statistical unification of tournaments, that is, has not absorbed to the Intercontinental Cup (merged with FIFA Club World Cup in 2005), FIFA is the only organization with worldwide jurisdiction over continental confederations and, then, the only one that can confer a title on that level, ergo the title assigned by FIFA with Official Document to the winners of the Intercontinental Cup is legally a FIFA world title.\"  cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|last=|first=|date=|website=|page=19|format=PDF|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}} cfr.</ref><ref name=\"FIFA201732\">{{cite press release|date=27 October 2017|title=FIFA Council approves key organisational elements of the FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/news/y=2017/m=10/news=fifa-council-approves-key-organisational-elements-of-the-fifa-world-cu-2917722.html|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/fifa-acepta-propuesta-de-conembol-de-reconocer-titulos-de-copa-intercontinental-como-mundiales-de|title=FIFA acepta propuesta de CONMEBOL de reconocer t\u00edtulos de copa intercontinental como mundiales de clubes|date=29 October 2017|publisher=conmebol.com|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"kit201822\">{{cite web|url=h